com.nkoiv.mists.game

Class Mists

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.application.Application
      • com.nkoiv.mists.game.Mists
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Global

    public class Mists
extends javafx.application.Application
implements Global
    Mists Class is used to initialize the window and launch the game. This class is intended to be easily rewritten when porting game to other platforms. Mists is the View of the game.
    Author:
    nkoiv

      • start

        public void start(javafx.stage.Stage primaryStage)
        start(), coming from the Application that Mists extends, is the call to launch the game. The main loop of the game is executed inside the start, with an AnimationTimer(); Everything shown on the screen is displayed via the priamaryStage, given to start by the Application.launch();
        Specified by:
        start in class javafx.application.Application
        Parameters:
        primaryStage - Comes from the Application class, as called for in the main(): Application.launch();
